Package com.dougnoel.sentinel.elements.tables

Class Table

java.lang.Object
com.dougnoel.sentinel.elements.Element
com.dougnoel.sentinel.elements.tables.Table
Direct Known Subclasses:
NGXDataTable
public class Table
extends Element
Implements a Table WebElement. contains functionality for counting values, finding values inside a table, and other management issues, such as finding a value in the same row.

  • Constructor Details

    • Table

      public Table​(java.lang.String elementName, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> selectors)
      Creates a table object to manipulate. When used the table object finds and creates rows and columns and stores them. If data in the table changes you must use the reset() method. You can save the current state of a table by calling the storeTable() method.
      Parameters:
      elementName - String the name of the element
      selectors - Map<String,String> the list of selectors to use to find the element

    • compareWithStoredTable

    • clickElementInRowThatContains

      public void clickElementInRowThatContains​(java.lang.String elementText, java.lang.String textToClick)
      Clicks a link in a row by using text in another cell. For example, finding an "Edit" link for a specific username in a table. To work, this method must have a link name and a unique string to match. This method could also be used to validate text in a cell in the same row Returning successfully would indicate the expected text was found.
      Parameters:
      elementText - String the text of the element (link) you are looking to find
      textToClick - String the unique text to locate the row in question

    • verifySpecificCellContains

      public java.lang.String verifySpecificCellContains​(java.lang.String columnHeader, int rowIndex, java.lang.String textToMatch, boolean partialMatch)
      Returns null if the cell in the given column and row match the text value given. Otherwise, returns the actual text of the given cell.
      Parameters:
      columnHeader - String the name of the column
      rowIndex - int the index of the row
      textToMatch - String the text that should be in the specified cell
      partialMatch - boolean if true, this method returns null if the actual cell text contains the given textToMatch. if false, this method returns null when the actual cell text exactly matches the given textToMatch.
      Returns:
      String null if the text of the cell given by the passed column + row contains or exactly matches (depending on partialMatch parameter) the given text. Otherwise, returns the actual text of the given cell.

    • verifyColumnCellsAreSorted

      public boolean verifyColumnCellsAreSorted​(java.lang.String columnName, boolean sortOrderAscending)
      Checks all the cells in a given column and verifies they are sorted in requested Comparator order.

      NOTE: Use the verifyColumnCellsAreSortedAscending() and verifyColumnCellsAreSortedDescending() methods unless you have a custom sort to pass. Passing the wrong value can cause errors.

      Parameters:
      columnName - String the name of the column you want to evaluate
      sortOrderAscending - boolean true for ascending, false for descending
      Returns:
      boolean true is the column is sorted in the passed sort order, false if it is not sorted correctly

      Returns true if the table has a column header that's equal to the given text. false if the table does not have a column header that's equal to the given text.
      Parameters:
      columnName - String name of column to find
      partialMatch - boolean if true, this method returns true if the actual header contains the given columnHeader. * if false, this method returns true when the actual header exactly matches the given columnHeader.
      Returns:
      boolean true if column equals, false if column is not equal.

    • waitForSpecificCellToContain

      public boolean waitForSpecificCellToContain​(int numberOfSecondsToWait, java.lang.String columnHeader, int rowIndex, java.lang.String textToMatch, boolean partialMatch, boolean negate)
      Waits the given amount of seconds until the given cell does or does not have the given text in it.
      Parameters:
      numberOfSecondsToWait - int number of seconds to wait for the desired condition.
      columnHeader - String name of the column.
      rowIndex - int index of the row, starting at 1.
      textToMatch - String text to look for in the cell.
      partialMatch - boolean if the match should be "contains" or "equals". if true, contains. if false, equals.
      negate - boolean true if this method should return once the text is NOT found in the cell.
      Returns:
      boolean true if the text to search for is found within the given timeout, false otherwise.
